sentences: Usman Warsi (Urdu:  عثمان وارثی) (born September 23, 1972 in Lahore, Pakistan) is a singer, a poet, a music director, and a composer.
Usman completed his studies in 1999 in Lahore.
Usman's song "Yeh Mera Dil" was aired from all the major channels of Pakistan in 2003 i.e. PTV, PTV Prime and some private channels.
Interview published in Daily Mashriq on January 25, 1991.
Usman joined Sayyed Noor's company Paragon as music director and composer on January 1, 2000.
Popularity of his song "Yeh Mera Dil", Nawa-i-Waqt, March 2, 2003.
About making of song videos with all actors from UK and Canada, Nawa-i-Waqt, January 21, 2003.
Background music of the drama Gaddagar given by Usman Warsi and directed by Rukhsana Noor (film director), Nawa-i-Waqt, May 11, 2004.
About making of song videos and their release before Basant festival in the daily Nawa-i-Waqt, January 26, 2003.
He has created backgrounds for TV serials and has written and composed many songs in his 18 year long carrer as a composer and arranger.
Usman got married in 1999 in Lahore.
He worked in Dubai between 2006 and 2010 and he now lives in Saudi Arabia.
